Innovate solutions that will enable development of vehicles incapable of causing a crash, regardless of the actions of the driver. Develop technology for vehicles and robots to help people enjoy new levels of independence, access, and mobility. Bring advanced mobility technology to market faster Discover new materials that will make batteries and hydrogen fuel cells smaller, lighter, less expensive and more powerful. Develop human-centered AI systems to augment (not replace) human decision making to increase the quality of decisions (e.g. mitigate cognitive biases) and/or to facilitate faster innovation cycles. 
If this sounds exciting to you, join our 12-week Summer 2021 Internship Program. Our program allows you to work on real projects around designing safer cars, enabling the elderly to age in place with the help of robots, crafting alternative fuel sources, and developing new science to better understand human cognition. Interns will benefit from an encouraging, collaborative environment and gain insights from a dedicated mentor who will help ensure a productive and meaningful experience. You will work as part of a team to perform basic research and development on component technologies for machine learning, perception/computer vision, controls, planning, simulation, and other critical areas of investigation. Interns will also benefit from networking with other interns and employees, participating in technical teach -ins, and interacting with senior leadership. 
If you are a creative problem solver and an innovator with a strong desire to apply your technical skills to research which can improve the quality of human life,  this is the internship for you! 
 Responsibilities:
 You will perform basic research and development as part of the TRI Research Team 
Assist in projects specifically focused on machine learning, perception/computer vision, controls, planning, simulation, and other areas of investigation defined by the teams. 
Operate independently to pursue research topics and identify new areas for investigation. 
Extend the boundaries of scientific understanding in your field of study. 
Write and publish research findings in top scientific conferences and journals. 
 Qualifications:
 BS, MS, PhD Degree in a relevant field. 
Research and project work that is closely aligned with the areas of interest to TRI including autonomous driving, robotics, accelerated materials design and development, and machine assisted cognition. 
Demonstrated creativity and innovation and desire to see research discoveries brought to life in new products and services. 
Comfort operating in an environment where openness, curiosity, and humility are highly valued. 
Ability to work in a team including software and communication skills. 
Interest in learning from others while contributing to TRI‚Äôs vibrant research community. 
